SCOTLAND NORTH AND WEST COASTS. CAPE WRATH AND NORTH MINCH.
1. INTERMITTENT GPS JAMMING EXERCISE IN PROGRESS 05 TO 17 OCT DAYLIGHT
HOURS ONLY IN FOLLOWING AREAS:
A) WITHIN 36 MILES OF FARAID HEAD 58-36.2N 004-46.5W IN AN ARC FROM
270 DEGREES CLOCKWISE TO 100 DEGREES.
B) WITHIN 28 MILES OF LOCH EWE 57-51.9N 005-41.1W IN AN ARC FROM 285
DEGREES CLOCKWISE TO 040 DEGREES.
2. ALTERNATIVE MEANS OF NAVIGATION SHOULD BE USED DURING JAMMING PERIODS
TO CONFIRM POSITION. GPS EQUIPMENT SHOULD BE CHECKED FOR CORRECT OPERATION
EITHER WHEN CLEAR OF THE AFFECTED AREAS OR ON COMPLETION OF THE EXERCISE.
3. IN AN EMERGENCY JAMMING MAY BE STOPPED ON REQUEST VIA THE JAMMING UNIT
ON 01436 674321 EXT. 4372 OR CRC BOULMER MASTER CONTROLLER ON 01665 572311.
4. JAMMING WILL NOT TAKE PLACE IN RESTRICTED VISIBILITY.
5. CANCEL THIS MESSAGE 172359 UTC OCT 19.
